{"title_page": "Sjoerd Vollebregt", "text_new": "{{Infobox sailor\n| name           = Sjoerd Vollebregt\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| birth_name     = \n| fullname       = Sjoerd Steven Vollebregt\n| nickname       = \n| nationality    = Dutch\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1954|12|10|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Leiden]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = {{convert|1.85|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| weight         = \n| classes        = [[470 (dinghy)|470]]<br />[[Flying Dutchman (dinghy)|Flying Dutchman]]<br />[[Soling]]\n| club           = Koninklijke Watersport Vereniging <br /> De Kaag\n| collegeteam    = \n| coach          = \n| medaltemplates-title = Competition record\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry | {{NED}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[Olympic Games]] }}\n{{MedalGold | [[Sailing at the 1976 Summer Olympics|1976 Montreal]] | [[Sailing at the 1976 Summer Olympics \u2013 Flying Dutchman|Flying Dutchman]] }}\n{{MedalGold | [[Sailing at the 1980 Summer Olympics|1980 Moscow]] | [[Sailing at the 1980 Summer Olympics \u2013 Flying Dutchman|Flying Dutchman]] }}\n{{MedalCompetition | World Championships }}\n{{MedalGold | 1972 [[Montreal]] | [[470 (dinghy)|470]] }}\n{{MedalBronze | 1977 [[Nago-Torbole|Torbole]] | [[Flying Dutchman (dinghy)|Flying Dutchman]] }}\n{{MedalBronze | 1979 [[Kiel]] | [[Flying Dutchman (dinghy)|Flying Dutchman]] }}\n| show-medals    = yes\n| updated        = 13 February 2014\n}}\n\n'''Sjoerd Steven Vollebregt''' (born 10 December 1954, in [[Leiden]]<ref name=\"A\" />) is a [[sailor]] from the Netherlands who represented his native country at the [[Sailing at the 1976 Summer Olympics \u2013 Flying Dutchman|1976 Summer Olympics]] in [[Kingston, Ontario]].<ref name=\"B\" /><ref name=\"C\" /> With twin brother [[Erik Vollebregt]] as helmsman, Vollebregt finished 14th in the [[Sailing at the 1976 Summer Olympics \u2013 Flying Dutchman]]. Since in [[Sailing at the 1980 Summer Olympics|1980]] the  Netherlands [[1980 Summer Olympics boycott|boycotted]] the Moscow Olympics, Vollebregt represented<ref name=\"E\" /> his National Olympic Committee under the Dutch [[NOC*NSF|NOC]] flag in the [[Sailing at the 1980 Summer Olympics \u2013 Flying Dutchman|Flying Dutchman]]. Again with his brother as helmsman, he took 7th place.<ref name=\"F\" /><ref name=\"G\" />\n\nAfter the 1980 Olympics Vollebregt started a new Olympic campaign for the [[Sailing at the 1984 Summer Olympics|1984 Olympics]] crewing in the [[Soling]] together with [[Gijs Evers]] and his older brother [[Peter Vollebregt]] as helmsman but finally failed to qualify.\n\n==Controversions==\n* '''1976:'''\n:During the selection for the [[Dutch Olympic Sailing Team]] for the [[Sailing at the 1976 Summer Olympics|1976 Olympics]] a controversy<ref name=\"D\" /><ref name=\"H\" /> emerged between twelve sailors and the [[Koninklijk Nederlands Watersport Verbond|selection committee]] chaired by [[Andr\u00e9 du Pon]]. [[Fred Imhoff]] and [[Heike Blok]], two sailors hoping to be selected, filed suit, arguing that [[Frieda Vollebergt]],<ref name=\"I\" /> the communications person for the sailing team, was partial: as mother of Erik, Sjoerd, and [[Peter Vollebregt]], all candidates for the 1976 Olympic sailing event, she was accused for having a bias towards her children. In the end<ref name=\"J\" /> Imhoff and Blok lost the [[lawsuit]]<ref name=\"K\" /><ref name=\"L\" /><ref name=\"M\" /><ref name=\"N\" /> and were removed from the 1976 selection.<ref name=\"O\" /> During this period Vollebregt's father, [[Jan Vollebregt]], was president of the [[Koninklijk Nederlands Watersport Verbond]] (Dutch Yacht Racing Union).\n* '''1980:'''\n:Several countries<ref name=\"P\" /> did [[1980 Summer Olympics boycott|boycott]] the [[Sailing at the 1980 Summer Olympics|1980 Summer Olympics]], others like [[France]] did not go since they found the competition devaluated. As result only half of the expected fleet was present during the Olympic regattas.\n\n==Further reading==\n\n===[[Sailing at the 1976 Summer Olympics|1976 Olympics (Kingston)]] {{flagIOC|CAN|1976 Summer}}===\n* {{cite web\n  | url        = http://library.la84.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1976/1976v1.pdf\n  | title      = Montr\u00e9al 1976 Official Report,Volume I: Organization\n  | publisher  = COJO\n  | location   = Ottawa\n  | year       = 1978\n  | format     = PDF\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}\n* {{cite web\n  | url        = http://library.la84.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1976/1976v2.pdf\n  | title      = Montr\u00e9al 1976 Official Report,Volume II: Facilities\n  | publisher  = COJO\n  | location   = Ottawa\n  | year       = 1978\n  | format     = PDF\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}\n* {{cite web\n  | url        = http://library.la84.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1976/1976v3.pdf\n  | title      = Montr\u00e9al 1976 Official Report,Volume III: Results\n  | publisher  = COJO\n  | location   = Ottawa\n  | year       = 1978\n  | format     = PDF\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}\n\n===[[Sailing at the 1980 Summer Olympics|1980 Olympics (Tallinn)]] {{flagIOC|URS|1980 Summer}}===\n* {{cite web\n  | url        = http://library.la84.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1980/or1980v1.pdf\n  | title      = Games of the XXII Olympiad,Volume I: Moscow, Tallinn, Leningrad, Kiev and Minsk\n  | publisher  = Fizkultura i Sport Publishers\n  | year       = 1981\n  | format     = PDF\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}\n* {{cite web\n  | url        = http://library.la84.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1980/or1980v2.pdf\n  | title      = Games of the XXII Olympiad,Volume II: Organisation\n  | publisher  = Fizkultura i Sport Publishers\n  | year       = 1981\n  | format     = PDF\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}\n* {{cite web\n  | url        = http://library.la84.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1980/or1980v3.pdf\n  | title      = Games of the XXII Olympiad,Volume III: Participants and Results\n  | publisher  = Fizkultura i Sport Publishers\n  | year       = 1981\n  | format     = PDF\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"A\">{{cite web\n  | url        = https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/vo/sjoerd-vollebregt-1.html\n  | title      = Sjoerd Vollebregt Bio, Stats, and Results\n  | publisher  = Sports-Reference.com\n  | accessdate = 2014-01-09\n}}</ref>\n <ref name=\"B\">{{cite news\n  | url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:010620261:mpeg21:a0244\n  | title      = Nederlandse delegatie\n  | newspaper  = [[Leeuwarder Courant]]\n  | language   = Dutch\n  | date       = 12 July 1976\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}</ref>\n <ref name=\"C\">{{cite news\n  | url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:011200804:mpeg21:a0338\n  | title      = Olympische zeilselectie\n  | newspaper  = [[De Telegraaf]]\n  | date       = 20 May 1976\n  | language   = Dutch\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}</ref>\n <ref name=\"D\">{{cite news\n  | url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:011198880:mpeg21:a0380\n  | title      = Verwijt\n  | newspaper  = De Telegraaf\n  | date       = 22 August 1975\n  | language   = Dutch\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}</ref>\n <ref name=\"H\">{{cite news\n  | url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:011198921:mpeg21:a0331\n  | title      = Zeiltop zit in het nauw\n  | newspaper  = De Telegraaf\n  | date       = 9 October 1975\n  | language   = Dutch\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}</ref>\n <ref name=\"J\">{{cite news\n  | url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:010620180:mpeg21:a0415\n  | title      = Fred Imhoff in kort geding tegen KNWV\n  | newspaper  = Leeuwarder courant : hoofdblad van Friesland\n  | date       = 9 October 1975\n  | language   = Dutch\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}</ref>\n <ref name=\"K\">{{cite news\n  | url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:011200005:mpeg21:a0375\n  | title      = Uitslag proces: Fred Imhoff niet terug in kernploeg\n  | newspaper  = De Telegraaf\n  | date       = 9 April 1976\n  | language   = Dutch\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}</ref>\n <ref name=\"L\">{{cite news\n  | url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:010620068:mpeg21:a0337\n  | title      = Imhoff en Blok uit Olympische zeilploeg gezet\n  | newspaper  = Leeuwarder courant : hoofdblad van Friesland\n  | date       = 2 April 1976\n  | language   = Dutch\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}</ref>\n <ref name=\"M\">{{cite news\n  | url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:010959180:mpeg21:a0337\n  | title      = Imhoff\n  | newspaper  = Het vr\u0133e volk : democratisch-socialistisch dagblag\n  | date       = 9 April 1976\n  | language   = Dutch\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}</ref>\n <ref name=\"N\">{{cite news\n  | url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:011200011:mpeg21:a0340\n  | title      = Imhoff heeft nog kleine kans\n  | newspaper  = De Telegraaf\n  | date       = 16 April 1976\n  | language   = Dutch\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}</ref>\n <ref name=\"I\">{{cite news\n  | url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:110592979:mpeg21:a0382\n  | title      = Mevrouw Vollebregt centraal in zeilrel\n  | newspaper  = De Telegraaf\n  | date       = 23 April 1976\n  | language   = Dutch\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}</ref>\n <ref name=\"O\">{{cite news\n  | url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:011200023:mpeg21:a0286\n  | title      = Du Pon ziet nieuwe mogelijkheden TOPZEILERS WEER IN KERNPLOEG\n  | newspaper  = De Telegraaf\n  | date       = 1 December 1976\n  | language   = Dutch\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}</ref>\n <ref name=\"E\">{{cite news\n  | url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:011200725:mpeg21:a0404\n  | title      = Zeilers: ,We gaan\u2019\n  | newspaper  = De Telegraaf\n  | date       = 16 May 1980\n  | language   = Dutch\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}</ref>\n <ref name=\"F\">{{cite news\n  | url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:010621466:mpeg21:a0214\n  | title      = Zeilploeg bleef buiten de medailles\n  | newspaper  = De Telegraaf\n  | date       = 30 July 1980\n  | language   = Dutch\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}</ref>\n <ref name=\"G\">{{cite news\n  | url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:010984980:mpeg21:a0092\n  | title      = Staartjes: \"Het heeft niet meegezeten\" Geen medailles voor Nederlandse zeilers\n  | newspaper  = De waarheid\n  | date       = 31 July 1980\n  | language   = Dutch\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}</ref>\n <ref name=\"P\">{{cite news\n  | url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:010639894:mpeg21:a0099\n  | title      = Franse zeilploeg blijft thuis\n  | newspaper  = Amigoe\n  | date       = 22 May 1980\n  | language   = Dutch\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{Footer World Champions Men's 470}}\n{{1976DutchOlympicSailingTeam}}\n{{1980DutchOlympicSailingTeam}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vollebregt, Sjoerd}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1954 births]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Leiden]]\n[[Category:Dutch male sailors (sport)]]\n\n[[Category:470 class world champions]]\n[[Category:Soling Sailors]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 1976 Summer Olympics \u2013 Flying Dutchman]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 1980 Summer Olympics \u2013 Flying Dutchman]]\n[[Category:Olympic sailors of the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1980 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1976 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic gold medalists for the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:World champions in sailing for the Netherlands]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox sailor\n| name           = Sjoerd Vollebregt\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| birth_name     = \n| fullname       = Sjoerd Steven Vollebregt\n| nickname       = \n| nationality    = Dutch\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1954|12|10|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Leiden]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = {{convert|1.85|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| weight         = \n| classes        = [[470 (dinghy)|470]]<br />[[Flying Dutchman (dinghy)|Flying Dutchman]]<br />[[Soling]]\n| club           = Koninklijke Watersport Vereniging <br /> De Kaag\n| collegeteam    = \n| coach          = \n| medaltemplates-title = Competition record\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry | {{NED}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[Olympic Games]] }}\n{{MedalGold | [[Sailing at the 1976 Summer Olympics|1976 Montreal]] | [[Sailing at the 1976 Summer Olympics \u2013 Flying Dutchman|Flying Dutchman]] }}\n{{MedalGold | [[Sailing at the 1980 Summer Olympics|1980 Moscow]] | [[Sailing at the 1980 Summer Olympics \u2013 Flying Dutchman|Flying Dutchman]] }}\n{{MedalCompetition | World Championships }}\n{{MedalGold | 1972 [[Montreal]] | [[470 (dinghy)|470]] }}\n{{MedalBronze | 1977 [[Nago-Torbole|Torbole]] | [[Flying Dutchman (dinghy)|Flying Dutchman]] }}\n{{MedalBronze | 1979 [[Kiel]] | [[Flying Dutchman (dinghy)|Flying Dutchman]] }}\n| show-medals    = yes\n| updated        = 13 February 2014\n}}\n\n'''Sjoerd Steven Vollebregt''' (born 10 December 1954, in [[Leiden]]<ref name=\"A\" />) is a [[sailor]] from the Netherlands who represented his native country at the [[Sailing at the 1976 Summer Olympics \u2013 Flying Dutchman|1976 Summer Olympics]] in [[Kingston, Ontario]].<ref name=\"B\" /><ref name=\"C\" /> With twin brother [[Erik Vollebregt]] as helmsman, Vollebregt finished 14th in the [[Sailing at the 1976 Summer Olympics \u2013 Flying Dutchman]]. Since in [[Sailing at the 1980 Summer Olympics|1980]] the  Netherlands [[1980 Summer Olympics boycott|boycotted]] the Moscow Olympics, Vollebregt represented<ref name=\"E\" /> his National Olympic Committee under the Dutch [[NOC*NSF|NOC]] flag in the [[Sailing at the 1980 Summer Olympics \u2013 Flying Dutchman|Flying Dutchman]]. Again with his brother as helmsman, he took 7th place.<ref name=\"F\" /><ref name=\"G\" />\n\nAfter the 1980 Olympics Vollebregt started a new Olympic campaign for the [[Sailing at the 1984 Summer Olympics|1984 Olympics]] crewing in the [[Soling]] together with [[Gijs Evers]] and his older brother [[Peter Vollebregt]] as helmsman but finally failed to qualify.\n\n==Controversions==\n* '''1976:'''\n:During the selection for the [[Dutch Olympic Sailing Team]] for the [[Sailing at the 1976 Summer Olympics|1976 Olympics]] a controversy<ref name=\"D\" /><ref name=\"H\" /> emerged between twelve sailors and the [[Koninklijk Nederlands Watersport Verbond|selection committee]] chaired by [[Andr\u00e9 du Pon]]. [[Fred Imhoff]] and [[Heike Blok]], two sailors hoping to be selected, filed suit, arguing that [[Frieda Vollebergt]],<ref name=\"I\" /> the communications person for the sailing team, was partial: as mother of Erik, Sjoerd, and [[Peter Vollebregt]], all candidates for the 1976 Olympic sailing event, she was accused for having a bias towards her children. In the end<ref name=\"J\" /> Imhoff and Blok lost the [[lawsuit]]<ref name=\"K\" /><ref name=\"L\" /><ref name=\"M\" /><ref name=\"N\" /> and were removed from the 1976 selection.<ref name=\"O\" /> During this period Vollebregt's father, [[Jan Vollebregt]], was president of the [[Koninklijk Nederlands Watersport Verbond]] (Dutch Yacht Racing Union).\n* '''1980:'''\n:Several countries<ref name=\"P\" /> did [[1980 Summer Olympics boycott|boycott]] the [[Sailing at the 1980 Summer Olympics|1980 Summer Olympics]], others like [[France]] did not go since they found the competition devaluated. As result only half of the expected fleet was present during the Olympic regattas.\n\n==Further reading==\n\n===[[Sailing at the 1976 Summer Olympics|1976 Olympics (Kingston)]] {{flagIOC|CAN|1976 Summer}}===\n* {{cite web\n  | url        = http://library.la84.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1976/1976v1.pdf\n  | title      = Montr\u00e9al 1976 Official Report,Volume I: Organization\n  | publisher  = COJO\n  | location   = Ottawa\n  | year       = 1978\n  | format     = PDF\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}\n* {{cite web\n  | url        = http://library.la84.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1976/1976v2.pdf\n  | title      = Montr\u00e9al 1976 Official Report,Volume II: Facilities\n  | publisher  = COJO\n  | location   = Ottawa\n  | year       = 1978\n  | format     = PDF\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}\n* {{cite web\n  | url        = http://library.la84.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1976/1976v3.pdf\n  | title      = Montr\u00e9al 1976 Official Report,Volume III: Results\n  | publisher  = COJO\n  | location   = Ottawa\n  | year       = 1978\n  | format     = PDF\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}\n\n===[[Sailing at the 1980 Summer Olympics|1980 Olympics (Tallinn)]] {{flagIOC|URS|1980 Summer}}===\n* {{cite web\n  | url        = http://library.la84.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1980/or1980v1.pdf\n  | title      = Games of the XXII Olympiad,Volume I: Moscow, Tallinn, Leningrad, Kiev and Minsk\n  | publisher  = Fizkultura i Sport Publishers\n  | year       = 1981\n  | format     = PDF\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}\n* {{cite web\n  | url        = http://library.la84.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1980/or1980v2.pdf\n  | title      = Games of the XXII Olympiad,Volume II: Organisation\n  | publisher  = Fizkultura i Sport Publishers\n  | year       = 1981\n  | format     = PDF\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}\n* {{cite web\n  | url        = http://library.la84.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1980/or1980v3.pdf\n  | title      = Games of the XXII Olympiad,Volume III: Participants and Results\n  | publisher  = Fizkultura i Sport Publishers\n  | year       = 1981\n  | format     = PDF\n  | accessdate = 13 February 2014\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"A\">{{cite web\n  | url        = https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/vo/sjoerd-vollebregt-1.html\n  | title      = Sjoerd Vollebregt Bio, Stats, and Results\n  | publisher  = Sports-Reference.com\n  | accessdate =